    <note>
        <div>
            <p>Section 122 of the Foreign Relations Authorization Act for Fiscal Years 1992 and 1993
                (P.L. 102-138; 105 Stat. 658) authorized the appointment of an Assistant Secretary
                of State for South Asian Affairs on October 28, 1991. The Bureau of South Asian
                Affairs was established Aug 24, 1992, and is responsible for relations with India,
                Pakistan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Nepal, Bhutan, Afghanistan, and the Maldive
                Islands.</p>
        </div>
    </note>
